<subSubSection id="C35C9886FFC2FFA50380FAB2FCF74F14" lastPageId="34" lastPageNumber="35" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BF9CB0DFFC2FFA50380FAB2FCF74F14" blockId="33.[120,1226,785,1783]" lastBlockId="34.[120,1225,225,289]" lastPageId="34" lastPageNumber="35" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">
COMMENTS: 
<bibRefCitation id="EFD7B6FCFFC2FFA60217FAB2FD8D4B03" author="Koteja, J. &amp; D. Azar" box="[319,593,1308,1334]" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" pagination="133 - 167" refId="ref37646" refString="Koteja, J., and D. Azar. 2008. Scale insects from Lower Cretaceous amber of Lebanon (Hemiptera: Sternorrhyncha: Coccinea). Alavesia 167: 133 - 167." type="journal article" year="2008">Koteja and Azar (2008)</bibRefCitation>
tentatively classified 
<taxonomicName id="4C46B08EFFC2FFA60063FAB3FC194B02" authorityName=", Koteja and Azar" authorityYear="2008" box="[843,965,1309,1335]" class="Insecta" family="Electrococcidae" genus="Apticoccus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B932171FFFC2FFA60063FAB3FC194B02" box="[843,965,1309,1335]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Apticoccus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the family 
<taxonomicName id="4C46B08EFFC2FFA60742FAB2FF3C4B69" baseAuthorityName="Koteja" baseAuthorityYear="2000" class="Insecta" family="Electrococcidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Electrococcidae</taxonomicName>
. This family was created by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFD7B6FCFFC2FFA6010EFAECFD084B68" author="Koteja, J." box="[550,724,1346,1373]" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" pagination="147 - 229" refId="ref37531" refString="Koteja, J. 2000 b. Scale insects (Homoptera, Coccinea) from Upper Cretaceous New Jersey amber. In D. A. Grimaldi (editor), Studies on fossils in amber, with particular reference to the Cretaceous of New Jersey: 147 - 229. Leiden: Backhuys Publishers." type="book chapter" year="2000">Koteja (2000b)</bibRefCitation>
after the author described the genus 
<taxonomicName id="4C46B08EFFC2FFA607AFFAECFEEE4BB4" authority="Koteja" authorityName="Koteja" authorityYear="2000" class="Insecta" family="Hemiptera (awaiting allocation)" genus="Turonicoccus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B932171FFFC2FFA607AFFAECFF054BB4" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Turonicoccus</emphasis>
Koteja
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingRegion id="498205EFFFC2FFA602ADFAC9FDD24BB4" box="[389,526,1383,1409]" country="United States of America" name="New Jersey" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">New Jersey</collectingRegion>
amber and suggested that this genus and 
<taxonomicName id="4C46B08EFFC2FFA6070FFAC9FB1D4BB4" authorityName="Beardsley" authorityYear="1969" box="[1063,1217,1383,1409]" class="Insecta" family="Hemiptera (awaiting allocation)" genus="Electrococcus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B932171FFFC2FFA6070FFAC9FB1D4BB4" box="[1063,1217,1383,1409]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Electrococcus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, described from Canadian amber (
<bibRefCitation id="EFD7B6FCFFC2FFA6012FFA22FD1C4B92" author="Beardsley, J. W." box="[519,704,1420,1447]" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" pagination="270 - 279" refId="ref35389" refString="Beardsley, J. W. 1969. A new fossil scale insect (Homoptera: Coccoidea) from Canadian amber. Psyche 76: 270 - 279." type="journal article" year="1969">Beardsley, 1969</bibRefCitation>
), belong to the same family. The assignment of 
<taxonomicName id="4C46B08EFFC2FFA603B0FA1CFECE4BF9" authorityName=", Koteja and Azar" authorityYear="2008" box="[152,274,1458,1484]" class="Insecta" family="Electrococcidae" genus="Apticoccus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B932171FFFC2FFA603B0FA1CFECE4BF9" box="[152,274,1458,1484]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Apticoccus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to 
<taxonomicName id="4C46B08EFFC2FFA60212FA1CFE284BF9" baseAuthorityName="Koteja" baseAuthorityYear="2000" box="[314,500,1458,1484]" class="Insecta" family="Electrococcidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Electrococcidae</taxonomicName>
is, however, uncertain, according to 
<bibRefCitation id="EFD7B6FCFFC2FFA60084FA1CFB1F4BF9" author="Koteja, J. &amp; D. Azar" box="[940,1219,1458,1484]" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" pagination="133 - 167" refId="ref37646" refString="Koteja, J., and D. Azar. 2008. Scale insects from Lower Cretaceous amber of Lebanon (Hemiptera: Sternorrhyncha: Coccinea). Alavesia 167: 133 - 167." type="journal article" year="2008">Koteja and Azar (2008)</bibRefCitation>
, probably because of the poorly preserved 
<typeStatus id="54FD75AFFFC2FFA60146FA79FD044BC4" box="[622,728,1495,1521]" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">holotype</typeStatus>
. Based on newly studied material, we are creating the new family 
<taxonomicName id="4C46B08EFFC2FFA602B3FA52FDEF4823" authorityName="Vea &amp; Grimaldi" authorityYear="2015" box="[411,563,1532,1558]" class="Insecta" family="Apticoccidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Apticoccidae</taxonomicName>
for 
<taxonomicName id="4C46B08EFFC2FFA60140FA53FD3E4822" authorityName=", Koteja and Azar" authorityYear="2008" box="[616,738,1533,1559]" class="Insecta" family="Electrococcidae" genus="Apticoccus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B932171FFFC2FFA60140FA53FD3E4822" box="[616,738,1533,1559]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Apticoccus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, based on the following differences with 
<taxonomicName id="4C46B08EFFC2FFA60350F98CFED2480E" authorityName="Koteja" authorityYear="2000" box="[120,270,1570,1595]" class="Insecta" family="Hemiptera (awaiting allocation)" genus="Turonicoccus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B932171FFFC2FFA60350F98CFED2480E" box="[120,270,1570,1595]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Turonicoccus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C46B08EFFC2FFA60267F98CFE3B4809" authorityName="Beardsley" authorityYear="1969" box="[335,487,1570,1596]" class="Insecta" family="Hemiptera (awaiting allocation)" genus="Electrococcus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B932171FFFC2FFA60267F98CFE3B4809" box="[335,487,1570,1596]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Electrococcus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
: head small and generally narrower than thorax (vs. head as large as thoracic structures), antennae without short, fleshy setae or capitate setae (vs. capitate setae and presence of short fleshy setae in 
<taxonomicName id="4C46B08EFFC2FFA6014DF9C3FD2748B3" authorityName="Koteja" authorityYear="2000" box="[613,763,1645,1670]" class="Insecta" family="Hemiptera (awaiting allocation)" genus="Turonicoccus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B932171FFFC2FFA6014DF9C3FD2748B3" box="[613,763,1645,1670]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Turonicoccus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), apical segments with bristles forming a brush (vs. absent), one tarsal segment (vs. two tarsal segments), scutellum rectangular, transverse and narrow (vs. enlarged rectangular scutellum), penial sheath spinelike (vs. shorter triangular penial sheath). The phylogenetic analysis retrieved 
<taxonomicName id="4C46B08EFFC2FFA60063F972FC3F48C3" authorityName="Vea &amp; Grimaldi" authorityYear="2015" box="[843,995,1756,1782]" class="Insecta" family="Apticoccidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Apticoccidae</taxonomicName>
as an independent, monophyletic lineage, sister group to all neococcoid families. Furthermore, 
<taxonomicName id="4C46B08EFFC1FFA500C6FF4CFBB44EC9" authorityName=", Koteja and Azar" authorityYear="2008" box="[1006,1128,226,252]" class="Insecta" family="Electrococcidae" genus="Apticoccus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B932171FFFC1FFA500C6FF4CFBB44EC9" box="[1006,1128,226,252]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">Apticoccus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was not found to be related to either 
<taxonomicName id="4C46B08EFFC1FFA502E5FEA9FDBF4F15" authorityName="Koteja" authorityYear="2000" box="[461,611,263,288]" class="Insecta" family="Hemiptera (awaiting allocation)" genus="Turonicoccus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B932171FFFC1FFA502E5FEA9FDBF4F15" box="[461,611,263,288]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">Turonicoccus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
or 
<emphasis id="B932171FFFC1FFA501A4FEA9FCF74F14" box="[652,811,263,289]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">
<taxonomicName id="4C46B08EFFC1FFA501A4FEA9FCFB4F14" authorityName="Beardsley" authorityYear="1969" box="[652,807,263,289]" class="Insecta" family="Hemiptera (awaiting allocation)" genus="Electrococcus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Electrococcus</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
